page.title: 08WYKEHAM Continued
page.content: About 50 acres of woodland on Estate, mainly Ash, Beech, Sycamore & Spruce. All Elms died of Dutch Elm Disease. Ongoing programme of clearing,thinning and replanting. Country Pursuits _ in addition to the fishing Pheasants are bred, but only to a limited degree, most of the birds being bought in chicks. Services _ Mains Water & Electricity: Sewage by Septic Tanks: Mail delivered daily by van but posting box 1 mile on main road: No public transport all residents relying on cars and almost all on telephone:Refuse collection weekly: Doctors at Binbrook (3m) or Louth (8m). Hospitals at Louth and Lincoln and Hospital Car Service available.
